summary_markdown: This data presents a comparative analysis of two computer brands, Dell and HP/Compaq, based on their share of a survey sample and customer repeat purchase rates. HP/Compaq represents a slightly larger portion of the survey sample at 30%, compared to Dell at 29%. However, Dell demonstrates a significantly higher customer loyalty, with 50% of its surveyed customers indicating they would make a repeat purchase. In contrast, HP/Compaq has a lower repeat purchase rate of 36%. The structure is comparative, highlighting key performance indicators for each brand to facilitate a direct assessment of their market presence and customer retention.
